HEADWORD: Photogen
<hw>Pho"to*gen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Photo-</ets>
+ <ets>-gen</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A light hydrocarbon
oil resembling kerosene. It is obtained by distilling coal, paraffin,
etc., and is used as a lubricant, illuminant, etc.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>photogene</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

